# HSSS app standards

- TypeScript strict. No `any` unless unavoidable at a library boundary.
- App Router only. Server Components by default; `"use client"` only for forms and browser APIs.
- Supabase via `@supabase/ssr`. No hardcoded keys. Env vars only.
- Data access through `lib/` modules and route handlers, not inline in pages.
- Tailwind for styling. Brand tokens: navy `#003A70`, navy-deep `#001B3D`, cyan `#00AEEF`.
- No emojis in UI or copy.
- No code comments unless required for non-obvious external API constraints.
- No decorative separators, banner comments, or dead code.
- Components in `components/`, one primary export per file, PascalCase filenames.
- Keep MVP scope tight: auth, profile, dashboard, orders, quotes, custom orders, contact.
